who should I give this clue to?

434
00:18:04,050 --> 00:18:05,090
- Me! - Rock-paper-scissors?

435
00:18:05,090 --> 00:18:07,220
- Yes, play rock-paper-scissors. - Rock-paper-scissors.

436
00:18:07,220 --> 00:18:08,660
Winner or loser?

437
00:18:08,660 --> 00:18:09,960
- The loser. - The one who loses?

438
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,260
- The one who loses? - I like that.

439
00:18:11,260 --> 00:18:12,260
- That I can do. - The loser.

440
00:18:12,260 --> 00:18:14,230
- Rock-paper-scissors. - Rock-paper-scissors.

441
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:15,930
- It's for the one who loses. - Okay, paper.

442
00:18:15,930 --> 00:18:17,470
- No, wait. - We lost.

443
00:18:17,470 --> 00:18:18,970
- The three of us lost. - Darn.

444
00:18:18,970 --> 00:18:20,040
- Of all days... - Okay.

445
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:21,670
- Rock-paper-scissors. - I win when I have to lose.

446
00:18:21,670 --> 00:18:22,840
It's always the other way around.

447
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:24,110
- Rock-paper-scissors. - Rock-paper-scissors.

448
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:25,680
It's always the other way around.

449
00:18:25,810 --> 00:18:27,850
- Of all days... - I win when I have to lose.

450
00:18:27,850 --> 00:18:29,450
- Unbelievable. - I'm here for you.

451
00:18:29,450 --> 00:18:30,710
Here's your clue.

452
00:18:30,710 --> 00:18:31,780
- Thank you. - Of all days...

453
00:18:31,780 --> 00:18:35,150
All I ask is that you do a good job finding it.

454
00:18:35,150 --> 00:18:36,250
- Thank you. - Right.

455
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:37,860
Shin Yang, your work is amazing.

456
00:18:38,390 --> 00:18:40,820
When I have to lose, I win. Unbelievable.

457
00:18:41,460 --> 00:18:43,130
- You can't even tell what it means. - I can.

458
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:45,500
- She won't know what it means. - I do know.

459
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:46,900
- Ji Hyo, please. - I got it.

460
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:48,300
- Please! - Haha, did you get a look at it?

461
00:18:48,870 --> 00:18:52,070
All I ask is that you do a good job finding it.

462
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:53,400
See you later, Shin Yang!

463
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:54,640
Sure. Start deducting.

464
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:55,770
- Right. - Wish us luck.

465
00:18:58,210 --> 00:18:59,210
As in up?

466
00:18:59,580 --> 00:19:01,210
There's nothing up there.

467
00:19:05,650 --> 00:19:06,680
Not up there?

468
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:08,220
Got it.

469
00:19:09,450 --> 00:19:10,490
Is it this?

470
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,120
Behind? Where?

471
00:19:19,060 --> 00:19:20,960
Gosh, thanks.

472
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:22,530
Now I'm scared.

473
00:19:25,470 --> 00:19:26,570
"The Scream" by Munch.

474
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:28,840
Thank you so much. You're the best.

475
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:31,310
I have a lot of the artwork now.

476
00:19:31,540 --> 00:19:33,080
Only one of them is authentic.

477
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:34,980
I wonder where it is.

478
00:19:35,350 --> 00:19:36,910
- Unbelievable. - Okay!

479
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:38,620
- I mean... - Shin Yang is impressive.

480
00:19:38,620 --> 00:19:40,320
He sure is impressive.

481
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,150
- I agree. - He's painted so many works.

482
00:19:42,150 --> 00:19:43,790
