483
00:19:43,790 --> 00:19:44,860
Exactly.

484
00:19:44,860 --> 00:19:46,460
- He's amazing. - Over his career,

485
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:48,860
- he didn't sell a single piece. - Not even one.

486
00:19:48,860 --> 00:19:50,360
I know. Every single piece must mean a lot to him.

487
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:51,630
I'm lost for words.

488
00:19:51,630 --> 00:19:52,800
He hasn't had any formal training.

489
00:19:53,100 --> 00:19:54,230
- No formal training? - He just...

490
00:19:54,230 --> 00:19:55,500
He was born with the gift.

491
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:58,600
I was so immersed in his work, like I said,

492
00:19:58,600 --> 00:19:59,740
that I couldn't complete the mission.

493
00:19:59,940 --> 00:20:01,910
On top of that, this is way out of our league.

494
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:04,440
How did he find so many paintings?

495
00:20:04,740 --> 00:20:06,410
Rather than Shin Yang's work, I focused on the clues.

496
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:07,910
- To me, - Exactly.

497
00:20:07,910 --> 00:20:10,010
- this is a work of art. - He didn't look at the paintings.

498
00:20:10,010 --> 00:20:11,180
- You wouldn't understand them. - I wouldn't.

499
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:13,420
Are you a detective, or just playing dress-up for kindergarten?

500
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,490
- I'm a detective. - You look like a child.

501
00:20:15,490 --> 00:20:16,690
Tell me about it.

502
00:20:16,690 --> 00:20:18,690
- I didn't go to kindergarten. - Check out his clothes.

503
00:20:18,690 --> 00:20:21,120
